DIAGNOSIS. — Up to 
30 mm
(literature: 
41 mm
, de 
Saussure & Zehntner 1902
) long. Brown, posterior margin of tergites darker brownish, some specimens with traces of former green coloration. Surface of tergites glabrous, at high magnification small dot-like impressions become visible. Anal shield well-rounded (
Fig. 24A
), glabrous. Apical antennomere with 4 sensory cones (
Fig. 28A
). Third joint of posterior telopod broad, with well-rounded tip. Posterior side with around sclerotized teeth and 3 sclerotized spines (
Figs 24L
; 
2 G; 2 H
). Second joint with long and slim, weakly curved immovable digit, basally with 1 spine, distally at inner margin with numerous sclerotized spots (
Fig. 24K
). Two stridulation ribs on each male harp and 2 on each side of female washboard (
Figs 24F, H
; 
2 E; 2 E
). Anal shield with 2 locking carinae, first small, second more than 4. times longer than first (
Figs 24D
; 
2 D; 2 C
). Operculum of vulva minute, female possibly immature (
Fig. 24E
).

Body measurements: males (specimens): length up to 30.2 (largest broken), width of thoracic shield up to 1., height of thoracic shield up to 9.2. Females (
2 specimens
): length up to 27.2 (literature 41.0 mm), width up to 13.7, height up to 7.9.

Habitus: elongated, not high (
Figs 24A
; 
2 A; 2 A
). Tergites and anal shield without hair, but surface of tergite and anal shield at high magnification covered with small, irregular circular pits

Antennae: length of joints: 1>2>3=4= << (
Fig. 28A
), sixth joint longest, of cylindrical shape (
Fig. 28A
), apically with 1 row of sensilla basiconica, on tip bearing a disc with 4 () sensory cones (
Fig. 28A
). First joint remarkably broader than the others, short and with one groove (
Fig. 28A
). Sclerotized teeth at the base of joints 1-3, reaching not up to apical border. First joint apically on one side with 1 or 2 rows of sensilla basiconica (
Fig. 28B
).

